{
  "doc_id": "29399",
  "text": "Algorithms MCS, LexBFS and LexDFS, and more generally algorithm L-MLS for any labeling structure L for which the order on labels is total, compute a pmo of a connected chordal graph [CITATION_1] . Note that the definition of a labeling structure given in [CITATION_2] is less general than the definition given in this paper, but the proof of this result still holds here. We define Algorithm Moplex-MLS, which computes a pmo of a chordal graph, whether the order on labels is total or not, by adding a tie-breaking rule when choosing a vertex with a maximal label when the ordering fails to be total.",
